rest_of_day_open: it's only Tuesday - 3 more days of work, but starting to plan out what to do on the weekend. I do feel pretty chuffed about the VP decision, it's given me a huge boost to lighten the mood and actually feel enthused about the election. But apart from that, the weeks are very much the same, week to week.
critical_positive: I asked a lot of questions and got a personal view of how a teacher is dealing with going back to school. It was an interesting slice of life that I wouldn't have gotten otherwise. I felt my partner was relatively engaged and happy to answer my questions, without being very curious or interested about me
critical_negative: I felt like i had to drive the conversation - they pretty much only asked a couple questions about me and never came up with any new topics - I had to shift the conversation each time to go on to something new. I don't thinkj he had much of a sense of humor, or at least wasn't interesting in showing a very interesting personality.

rest_of_day_open: I'm starting a pre-planning week at work (I am a teacher). There still is a lot of unanswered questions on what we are doing, I have heard things I don't like and I don't think are safe, but ultimately I think they have my beset interest at mind and care about me. I am excited to get back in the classroom, but I want it to be safe.
critical_positive: I feel like the person I talked to have a lot of lived experiences and relatable advice to give and was very understanding of the situation I was place in. I think they understood the problems that teachers face and saw the bigger picture when it came to everything. I also think they were intelligent.
critical_negative: I found the other person to be a little controlling in the conversation and moving the topics at their leisure. They were the one that ran the show and didn't really leave room for flexibility, they had to be interrupted to get a point across to them. Maybe a little too controlling.
